cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.IR 

The paper focuses on the use of a state-of-the-art object detection framework, Faster R-CNN, in the context of fruit detection in orchards. This involves the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of data augmentation techniques and the practical deployment of the detection network, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of tiling approaches to operate over orchard data, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
